would or Beethoven manuscripts.

00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:12.090
So what was that little
experience like for you,

00:10:12.090 --> 00:10:13.610
because I got to watch
it and it was fun,

00:10:13.610 --> 00:10:17.080
and we enjoy provoking
that for sure.

00:10:19.310 --> 00:10:26.950
&gt;&gt; Peter Stumpf: Well, I mean it's
the manuscript issue is kind of,

00:10:26.950 --> 00:10:31.040
I mean I was shocked to see
that, because, you know,

00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:36.750
the issue with manuscripts is
that some of them are hidden away

00:10:36.750 --> 00:10:42.390
in private collections, in
somebody's personal library.

00:10:42.390 --> 00:10:47.290
So we don't have access to a
lot of manuscripts and in some

00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:48.830
in some cases we don't
even know where they are

00:10:48.830 --> 00:10:51.640
or if they even exist
for that reason.

00:10:51.640 --> 00:11:00.680
There's no real organizational
sort of entity that controls that.

00:11:00.680 --> 00:11:07.670
So to see that one I was really
surprised, because it's not

00:11:07.670 --> 00:11:13.360
