working with all the time.

00:13:29.510 --> 00:13:36.960
What about Marlboro offers an even
more unique festival atmosphere

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:39.610
for you?

00:13:39.610 --> 00:13:44.150
&gt;&gt; Peter Stumpf: Well, Marlboro
is actually completely unique

00:13:44.150 --> 00:13:45.640
as a festival.

00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:56.650 position:56%
In summer festivals there is a
range of different sort of concepts.

00:13:56.650 --> 00:14:01.810 position:56%
Some are educational, which
involve, you know, will have faculty

00:14:01.810 --> 00:14:03.380
and students and their lessons

00:14:03.380 --> 00:14:06.450
and student performances,
faculty performances.

00:14:06.450 --> 00:14:08.750
Some festivals are just
professional where you go

00:14:08.750 --> 00:14:10.790
when you perform chamber
music and oftentimes

00:14:10.790 --> 00:14:14.540
in those cases you're
playing with people you may

00:14:14.540 --> 00:14:20.160
or may not know very well, may have
played with before but maybe not.

00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:24.420
And you're playing in a short
period of time rehearsing

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:26.820
and rather quickly putting
together a repertoire

00:14:26.820 --> 00:14:28.970
and presenting it in a concert.

00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:34.040
So those are the two kind
of ends of the spectrum.

00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:41.310
Marlboro is kind of in a different
category, because the concept

00:14:41.310 --> 00:14:44.390
of it is it's seven weeks long.

00:14:44.390 --> 00:14:46.750
The first two weeks there
are no performances,

00:14:46.750 --> 00:14:48.600
so it's just rehearsal.

00:14:48.600 --> 00:14:52.790
Then the concerts begin from the
from the third week to the end

00:14:52.790 --> 00:14:58.090
of the festival, so they
cover a span of five weeks.

00:14:58.090 --> 00:15:03.960 position:56%
And the program is only determined
ten days in advance of the concerts.

00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:06.770
And the reason for
that is that the groups

00:15:06.770 --> 00:15:12.100
that are rehearsing
decide amongst themselves.

00:15:12.100 --> 00:15:16.040
You have complete control
over whether

00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:17.410
or not you perform something.

00:15:17.410 --> 00:15:22.270
You can spend the whole summer at
Marlboro and not perform at all.

00:15:22.270 --> 00:15:23.960
You could just rehearse.

00:15:23.960 --> 00:15:26.150
There's no requirement
to perform anything.

00:15:26.150 --> 00:15:32.090
So you only perform if you feel
inspired as a group to do so.

00:15:32.090 --> 00:15:37.450 position:56%
And of course most groups are aiming
towards that possibility, but,

00:15:37.450 --> 00:15:39.480
you know, it's not a requirement.

00:15:39.480 --> 00:15:44.260
So we have an option to not
perform, which means that it's only

00:15:44.260 --> 00:15:49.040
when it really feels right, you
know, that the group chooses

00:15:49.040 --> 00:15:50.800
to offer it for performance.

00:15:50.800 --> 00:15:52.940
Now having even if it's
offered for performance,

00:15:52.940 --> 00:15:56.370
it isn't necessarily selected,
because then they have

00:15:56.370 --> 00:15:59.910
to choose the program
that makes the most sense,

00:15:59.910 --> 00:16:03.590
as some pieces even be
offered and not chosen

00:16:03.590 --> 00:16:06.470
and those aren't performed.

00:16:06.470 --> 00:16:11.000
And you really have
much more rehearsal time

00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:15.080
than you would ever
have at most festivals.

00:16:15.080 --> 00:16:17.970
So it's completely
different in that sense,

00:16:17.970 --> 00:16:25.540
so the performances have a
different kind of aura about them.

00:16:25.540 --> 00:16:30.740
They're not a group that's
rehearsed very quickly

00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:32.270
and put something together.

00:16:32.270 --> 00:16:35.660
They're not formed to a music
a group that's played together

00:16:35.660 --> 00:16:41.340
for years, but they are a
group that's rehearsed a lot

00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:46.010
and spent a lot of time
together on preparing the piece

00:16:46.010 --> 00:16:49.440
and really not been under any
pressure to hurry to perform

00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:53.570
so they can really delve
into it in great depth.

00:16:53.570 --> 00:16:58.400
And then on top of all of
that, it's also a program

00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:01.150
that involves younger
players and older players.

00:17:01.150 --> 00:17:04.890
So there's a certain number
of older players who are kind

00:17:04.890 --> 00:17:10.170
of in a somewhat of a mentor role
that are in each one of the groups.

00:17:10.170 --> 00:17:12.120
There's one person like
that in each group,

00:17:12.120 --> 00:17:15.000
and the others are very
talented and young players,

00:17:15.000 --> 00:17:17.500
some very best from
around the world.

00:17:17.500 --> 00:17:25.480
And what the idea is to really have
it be encourage them to rehearse

00:17:25.480 --> 00:17:33.130 position:56%
as peers and to work as like just a
group of musicians working together.

00:17:33.130 --> 00:17:37.620
And the role of the mentor varies
from one group to the next,

00:17:37.620 --> 00:17:39.660
so depending on the group itself.

00:17:39.660 --> 00:17:43.050
If the group needs a lot of help
with something then they're there.

00:17:43.050 --> 00:17:44.730
If they don't, they don't.

00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:50.160
But then the person in that role
also plays somewhat of a role

00:17:50.160 --> 00:17:54.280
in deciding about whether the
group is offered for performance.

00:17:54.280 --> 00:17:59.250
But the group decides, they kind
of choose themselves to do that.

00:17:59.250 --> 00:18:01.300 position:56%
So that's just completely different.

00:18:01.300 --> 00:18:06.690
And this was the, you know, kind of
the brainchild of Rudolph Serkin,

00:18:06.690 --> 00:18:12.970
who had this idea and
it really is --

00:18:12.970 --> 00:18:19.460
there are other festivals that have
tried to sort of do similar things,

00:18:19.460 --> 00:18:22.430
but none of them do
exactly like this.

00:18:22.430 --> 00:18:24.490
This is totally unique.

